<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Warriors are being ripped off BIG time. To my knowldege, all they have is taunt and DPS to hold agro. One hard nuke, slow, tash, or failed mez and its bye bye mob. I have seen wariors get it back, but too many times I have had to STOP attacking so they can get agro off of me. I'm thinking &quot;Maybe I should just tank&quot;.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I will add to this (maybe) after I have read the responses.<br>
<br>
Now... <br>
<br>
The agro spells are nice, but you HAVE to know how to use them.  Most SKs I have met have no idea how they work.  For instance....<br>
If you put your visage up, it doesn't do dick right off the bat.  First, you have to taunt.  THEN the taunt has to be successful.  THEN it will add an increased number of points to your hate-listing, depending on which spell you use.  The drawback about this spell is that it pops JUST before it wears off.  This actually is best if the SK DOESN'T use it for himself.  If the SK is going to tank, he is much better off using his jolts since they are instant agro and fast recast (yes, about 7 secs.)  The visage is best used if it is used on ANOTHER toon that is tanking.  THEN the taunt will add 5, 10, or whatever on each successful taunt instead of one.<br>
<br>
Yes, Darkness is THE best agro spell, but it uses a LOT of manna.  I can sit there and chain cast my terror lines and use almost no manna and actually use them almost as fast as (even instead of) my taunt.  If I keep them both loaded, this is good, but I get some piss-poor nukes that will also add agro.  As an SK, I can build so much damn agro, its insane.<br>
<br>
Now, warriors are a tricky situation.  I think Sony was trying to ballence the classes by making them less able to generate agro by giving them so many more hitpoints.  I think you guys got gyped.  I wish I could cast my weap-proc buffs on you to help you get more, but I can't.  Now you DO get an agro point every time you hit with a weapon, so using a faster weapon with your DW will work in your favor, but you are right ... I can generate thousands of points in spells before a warrior can break 1000.<br>
I also think the rest of the group has to understand the limitations of the WARRIOR.  Keep in mind that they are paying for all these hitpoints they get with their reduced ability to hold agro.  As I have seen so many others say, you have to adjust your playing style to that.  Yes, with me tanking, you can nuke the fucking dogshit out of them, I will PROBABLY hold agro anyway.  If they DO get away, they will turn and walk to you since I have them snared anyway.  With a warrior, you MIGHT not be able to do that, and that is NOT the warrior's fault.  But you also have to remember that with no heals or slows, I'm dead FAST.  I have told healers when I tank big fights, give me a cele heal right away so I can get my taps and agro spells going.  Otherwise, im a dead SK and you will have to get someone else in there.  Sometimes they don't... I die.  I remember these people.  They are on my &quot;Do Not Call&quot; list.<br>
A warior at my level will probably do twice the damage and have twice the hitpoints of me.  He has better damage mitigation, wears better armor, has better weapons skill caps, and will actually do MORE DPS than I will.  However, I can hold agro better, outright avoid hits better, and build agro faster.  What it comes down to is which do you want in your tank?<br>
<br>
If your tank loses agro, don't jump on the tank and say &quot;OMG U R Teh suxxorz.&quot;  There are times that it will just happen.  THere are some groups that do such insane DPS with their casters that they NEED a SK or pally to generate agro fast enough.  Then again, if the tank is a warrior, settle for LESS damage so the warrior can do more dammage and hold agro.  It's a balance, and BOTH sides have to know how to make it work. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tibult>tibult</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www-personal.umich.edu/~nnettles/Nick1.gif" BORDER=0> at: 11/22/03 6:43 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daramineq>DaraminEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 217<br> <font color=#330000>(11/22/03 6:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1154.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tank Rant!!</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> There are a few tricks to holding agro as a warrior.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Please... No offense Tiff, but I think I know all about agro. Should I go through the routine I go through? No, there's no point, suffice to say, I use every bit of debuff transfer agro as I can get -- there's no magic there. Of course if taunt fails it doesn't help me. I disarm like a mofo, for what good it does. I'm close to the mob, I ghetto bash with my FB 4 shield if things are really going to hell and back.<br>
<br>
Does that mean the chanter can slow on inc and not feel the hurt on some pulls? Nope.<br>
<br>
Does that mean the necro can drop thule on a mob as it comes into camp and not be having to FD 5's later? Nope.<br>
<br>
Does that mean the wizard can chain-cast SoS? Fraid not.<br>
<br>
All those things are possible with a paladin tank in your average xp group.<br>
<br>
If you're saying you have some special trick that means you have no agro problems in those situations, spit it out.<br>
