<br>
By my math, the chance for success after 3 taunts assuming 60% taunt rate and independant events is 93.6%<br>
P(Success)=0.6<br>
P(Fail)=1-P(Success)=0.4<br>
P(Fail 3 attempts)=0.4*0.4*0.4=0.064<br>
P(Success 3 attempts)=1-P(Fail 3 attempts)=93.6%<br>
<br>
As a chanter, I like to pull and pull with tash (Hard) or slow (Normal).  Thats 1 less pong and if the warrior/SK/Pali gets a successful taunt off the bat, thats that much more agro for him.<br>
<br>
I tend not to slow on normal missions if I'm not pulling. Its a waste to land slow on a mob thats already at 50% and I can see the wiz next to me lining up that 6k bomb. If I can get a slow in before the mob is engaged I may or may not, depends on the group dynamic, often I'm better off just nuking.<br>
